      "span_text": "The hydroxymetronidazole/metronidazole ratio was sensitive enough to discriminate among normal individuals and those with a past or an ongoing HCV infection, confirming our previous report [CITATION_1] , but could not discriminate those individuals with a history of HCV infection from those harboring a chronic hepatitis and thus, at risk for a progressive liver disease."
